335. brevis: Horace is himself one of the first masters of the terse speech that sticks.

336. dociles and fideles are predicates and may be translated best by adverbs.

337. omne...manat·: Bentley suspected this to be a line soisted in by the monks‚ like many single hexameters in Juvenal. His suspicions are groundless here.

339. ne is the reading of most MSS. restored by Bentley for nec: it is here final, not imperative. velit has the support of the better MSS. and I do not see why we should not retain it: many of the best editors prefer volet.
